article.headline: Jacksonville 101, Mercer 97, OT
article.story: MACON, Ga. (AP) -- Jesse Kimbrough hit a 3-pointer with less than a second remaining to force overtime and scored six points in the extra period to lead Jacksonville past Mercer 101-97 on Friday night. James Florence scored 39 points to help Mercer (12-14 overall, 7-8 Atlantic Sun Conference) overcome an early 17-point deficit. But he missed the front end of a 1-and-1 with seven seconds left in regulation that would have given the Bears a four-point lead. Florence had been 11-for-11 from the line up to that point. The Dolphins (14-11, 10-5) hit their first six 3-point attempts in building their big first-half lead, and led 50-41 at halftime. Mercer trailed 66-59 before taking the lead on an 8-0 run capped by a 3-pointer by Ross Alacqua with 10:45 left. Alacqua's two free throws gave Mercer a 93-87 lead with 50 seconds left before Ben Smith and Kimbrough tied it with 3-pointers. Smith led Jacksonville with 28 points, including 6-for-9 from 3-point range. Kimbrough added 21.
